    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Mapo Tofu</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 block (14 ounces) firm tofu, cubed</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 pound ground pork or beef</li>
            <li>3 cloves garlic, minced</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon grated ginger</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons doubanjiang (spicy bean paste)</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon chili oil</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon sugar</li>
            <li>1 cup chicken or vegetable broth</li>
            <li>2 teaspoons cornstarch mixed with 2 tablespoons water (slurry)</li>
            <li>2 green onions, chopped (for garnish)</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon Sichuan peppercorns, toasted and ground (optional)</li>
            <li>Steamed rice for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Chinese</li>
            <li>Spicy</li>
            <li>Main Dish</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a large pan or wok, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add ground pork or beef and cook until browned.</li>
            <li>Add minced garlic and grated ginger to the pan, and saut√© until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Stir in doubanjiang (spicy bean paste), chili oil, soy sauce, and sugar. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Add cubed tofu to the pan and gently stir to coat the tofu with the sauce.</li>
            <li>Pour in chicken or vegetable broth and bring the mixture to a simmer.</li>
            <li>Add the cornstarch slurry to the pan, stirring gently to thicken the sauce.</li>
            <li>Simmer for a few minutes until the tofu is heated through and the sauce has thickened.</li>
            <li>Garnish with chopped green onions and ground Sichuan peppercorns (if using).</li>
            <li>Serve the Mapo Tofu over steamed rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Mapo Tofu!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

